By Li Zailei, southern weekend reporter

Southern weekend intern, Yan Liyuan

Associate Editor | Henin Ho

The husband lay in the hospital corridor for several days, Luo Xiaohua finally learned the test results, the husband nucleic acid test showed positive. Later, they had hoped to be hospitalized, but there were no beds and they had to move around abandoned treatment rooms and hallways.

On the afternoon of January 29, the hospital informed her that she was ready to be admitted. Luo Xiaohua is very happy, she told her husband, son, hope to give her husband a little encouragement, hope. But what she didn't dare tell her husband was that the beds were made available because one of her patients had just died.

But in the hospital first-line epidemic prevention scene, the medical staff has exhausted.

"Hospitalisation is now a very big problem, " said Zhao Liang (not his real name) , a intensive-care unit doctor at Wuhan Hankou Hospital, a designated hospital.

He said the group, which sees an average of six or seven patients a day, has reached the limit of the number of patients it can handle. In addition, there are many outpatient patients can not be admitted.

On January 24,2020, the Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Control Headquarters decided to fully implement the classified and classified medical treatment service for Febrile citizens, which will divert mild patients from designated fever clinics to community hospitals.

After the start of "grading diagnosis and treatment" , the number of patients queuing in the outpatient department of the major fixed-point hospitals in Wuhan decreased obviously, but the pressure of bed tension did not ease. In comparison, the community hospitals are short of medical facilities and materials.

1
Testing for remission is hard to come by

1

###Testing for remission is hard to come by

On the afternoon of January 29, the medical staff of the designated hospital, Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, said that hospital beds were tight, but the outpatient department could still see a doctor. Patients who had been transferred from other places lined up to get a number for their first visit, bring your own CT scan and blood work.

Although the shortage of nucleic acid test kits had eased a few days ago, supplies remained limited. Another medical staff told southern weekend that the number of nucleic acid test kits is limited and that the hospital has only 100 quotas a day.

"At present, our hospital wards and out-patient 'observation rooms' have been fully occupied, fever outpatient service as usual, critical The Adventure of the Resident Patient, please go to other hospitals. In front of the outpatient building of Wuhan No. 7 Hospital, a large notice saying "the beds are full" was posted, an undated notice, "stop nucleic acid testing today, " was attached, and several were posted.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
An undated notice was posted outside a designated hospital to stop nucleic acid testing. (Li Furong / photo)

Unless the kit has a quota, the test for COVID-19 pneumonia takes 3 to 5 days, no paper report, and the results are subject to a phone call. Positive results were reported by phone, negative results were not reported. When taking samples, the patients or their families need to leave accurate ID information and telephone number.

A patient's family, although the number of nucleic acid testing is limited, at least advance booking can be scheduled, now the biggest problem, or beds. He says a diagnosis must first be made before anyone can be admitted to the hospital, and the beds are full and new ones have to be lined up. GET NUCLEIC ACID testing confirmed results, need to report to the residence of the neighborhood, the neighborhood will report to the patient information, Unified Arrangements Ward.

At the same time, the volunteer rescue group set up by enthusiastic citizens in Wuhan is full of screen messages asking for "beds" . "It's full, " said one patient's family member.

2
"increased security is essential. "

2

###"increased security is essential. "

Doctors on the front lines are worried about more than beds.

Zhao Liang told southern weekend that there is no specific drug for COVID-19 pneumonia, mainly to support treatment, the environment, immunity, the condition of equipment on the treatment effect is very big.

Hankou Hospital, which is close to the south China Seafood Market, was set up as a designated hospital in the early days, first for convenience, but later found that the hospital facilities were not ideal. Oxygen supply is a big problem, Zhao Liang said, for example. Severe cases of breathing difficulties, in the absence of a specific drug, "oxygen therapy" can keep up, can directly affect the treatment of the big problem, but now there are difficulties in supply.

"It's one hundred and twenty thousand of the most important things to protect yourself, " he told southern weekly. Hankou Hospital medical staff have been infected several, are early do not understand the danger of COVID-19, did not do a good job of protection of the situation "down" . When the protective gear caught up, there were no more cases of infection among medical staff.

He observed that the current isolation measures in the hospital there is a big problem, patients'families in the absence of protective measures, access to out-patient clinics, intensive care units have a great risk. It's emotionally difficult to separate a patient who had The Adventure of the Resident Patient with a family member. He recommended that security be strengthened and that full-time staff be deployed to guard the area and isolate family members of new patients.

"security measures are necessary, " he said, noting that patients have left the intensive care unit on their own and returned home to get their things. "A lot has happened in the last few days that is simply incomprehensible. "

3
Wear a modified face mask and patch protective clothing

3

###Wear a modified face mask and patch protective clothing

In the hall of Baofeng Street Health Service Center in Hankou district, the nurse on duty, Zheng Guiping, takes the temperature of the visitors first.

In fact, in the early days, fever patients were mainly concentrated in the community hospitals, when a lot of patients, the community outpatient service is very stressful. On January 22, community hospitals were notified that fever patients needed to be treated in designated hospitals and that patients with a temperature of more than 37.3 degrees Celsius needed to be treated in designated hospitals. Fever patients are no longer admitted to community hospitals, and long queues form outside fever clinics in designated hospitals.

On 24 January, the National Health Commission took the lead in setting up a joint prevention and control mechanism, issuing a circular and a pilot program, requiring all localities to give full play to their community mobilization capabilities. Subsequently, the designated hospital and the Community Hospital linkage classification diagnosis and treatment mode started, mild patients began to the community hospital triage.

Now, community hospitals also have to deal with Febrile patients. According to the above-mentioned announcement, Wuhan city-wide emergency call for 6,000 parade and online taxi, as an emergency vehicle allocated to the central city of 1,159 communities, the use of unified dispatch by the Community Neighborhood Committees.

Under the graded treatment, the community is responsible for comprehensively screening fever patients in the community and sending them to the community hospital for screening and classification. For patients who need to be treated in designated hospitals, the community shall make uniform arrangements for the delivery of vehicles to designated hospitals; for patients who do not need to be sent to fever clinics, the communities shall implement self-isolation of patients at home, the community is responsible for the observation service at home.

Hankow district Baofeng Street Health Service Center Chief Physician Yang Qinghong, hospital staff all back to work, in addition to fever patients, other simple diseases normal consultation. Community hospitals, he says, have simpler equipment -- no CT machines, no breathing machines, no nucleic acid test kits -- and can only do routine blood tests. When a patient's temperature rises above normal on his first visit, a blood test at a community hospital can tell if he has a bacterial or viral infection. If it is a bacterial infection, it can be treated at a community hospital on site.

Yang Qinghong said that at present the biggest difficulty of the community hospital is the material shortage, "the clothes are all broken" , at the same time, the facility is also quite simple.

"It's mainly because they change frequently, " Zheng added, adding that the masks were relatively plentiful and lacked protective glasses. They went to the dental office of the clinic and modified the masks to cover their foreheads. Protective clothing is very short, each person only issued one, has been wearing a few days, they do not trust themselves, to the community hospital ultraviolet radiation equipment, hoping to play an anti-virus effect, "peace of mind. ". In addition, the quality of the protective clothing is worrying, legs, waist holes, they take the tape on the clothes to play a lot of patches.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The legs of the nurse's protective clothing have been taped. (Li Furong / photo)

The fever patient that goes to community hospital sees a doctor, register information without exception, include content such as age, address, family information, want to record one by one. If patients are found in the area, the medical staff of the Community Hospital will visit the patient's home for regular disinfection.

Special period, go to community hospital patient's point of view, also produce change. "Some people have a cold, but they don't dare to say they have a fever. One dose or the Other? It's hard to say, but they should be measured. " Zhang Yaxin, a nurse, said mild suspected patients would prescribe drugs to isolate themselves. Two vehicles will be arranged in each area. The residents'committee will be informed of the serious cases and the patients will be sent to designated hospitals.
